Figure 1
).

PLC also generates 1,2-diacylglycerol (DAG) that performs its signaling functions by binding and activating other proteins, including protein kinases C (PKC) and certain transient receptor potential (TRP) canonical (TRPC) channels, in particular TRPC1, that can interact with Orai1 and STIM1 to support SOCE (29, 34) (
Figure 1
).

